  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1582891568758-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1582891568758-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1582891568758-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1582891568758-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1582891568758-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel and finely slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>shallots</strong>, then peel and finely slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>in 600ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[800ml] </span>[1L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>red lentils</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1582891574383-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1582891574383-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1582891574383-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1582891574383-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1582891574383-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the green stalk[s] off your<strong> aubergine[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and discard, then slice lengthways, into strips</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> aubergine</strong> <strong>strips </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook, covered, for 10-12 min, turning occasionally until golden and tender</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle more oil if your pan is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1582891595227-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1582891595227-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1582891595227-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1582891595227-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1582891595227-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!) and cook for 1 min, then add the <strong>lentils</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat, and cook for 15-20 min or until the lentils are tender and starting to break down – this is your <strong>Sri Lankan-style coconut dal</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1582891599180-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1582891599180-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1582891599180-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1582891599180-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1582891599180-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, slice your<strong> green chilli[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half lengthways, then slice diagonally into strips</p><p>Peel and chop the<strong> remaining shallot[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> remaining garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1582891603427-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1582891603427-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1582891603427-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1582891603427-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1582891603427-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save a few leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar</strong>, <strong>black mustard seeds</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>sugar </strong>in a bowl – this is your <strong>pickling liquid</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1582891607321-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1582891607321-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1582891607321-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1582891607321-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1582891607321-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>aubergine is golden and tender, transfer it to kitchen paper<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced green chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>shallot wedges</strong> with the <strong>remaining ground turmeric </strong>and cook for 2-3 min</p><p>Return the<strong> cooked aubergine </strong>to the pan with the<strong> pickling liquid </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until all the liquid has evaporated – this is your <strong>aubergine pickle</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1582891611731-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1582891611731-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1582891611731-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1582891611731-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1582891611731-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Sri Lankan-style</strong> <strong>coconut dal</strong> with the<strong> basmati rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Top with the <strong>aubergine pickle</strong>, garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves </strong>and season with a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
